misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes that calling .close() on a Scanner object only releases the memory and resources associated with the Scanner instance itself.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: In Java, closing a Scanner that is wrapped around an InputStream (like System.in) also closes the underlying stream. Since System.in is a global resource for the duration of the program, closing it prevents any subsequent attempts to read from the console, even if a new Scanner is created.
